ai_enrichment.shortcut_solution:
Since the average is independent of the total number of people, assume $x=1$:

$$
\frac{15\times2+7.5\times5+2.5\times13}{2+5+13}
=
\frac{30+37.5+32.5}{20}
=
\frac{100}{20}
=
5
$$

The total sum is 180. The sum of the first two is 28. The remaining sum is 152. The average of the remaining 10 is

$$
\frac{152}{10}
=
15\frac{1}{5}
$$
